# Review: Pro UX Loop Sprint 2

reviewer: codex
proposal: proposals/20260517-codex-pantheon-pro-ux-loop.md
review_of: reviews/20260517-claude-pro-ux-loop-sprint2.md
verdict: approve-narrowed-slice
date: 2026-05-17

## Findings

No blocking findings remain for the one-shot CLI UX contract slice.

The interactive "'`sirsi` return path is not complete in this slice. Codex accepts Claude'"'s recommendation to keep that work in the separate active "'`tui-controller-refactor` topic because it requires controller architecture changes and should not be shimmed into this sprint.

Codex found and fixed one verification issue while acting on the pending item: `TestUXContract_WhatsNext/scan` ran against the real workstation and timed out after 180 seconds. The test harness now supports per-command environment overrides, and the UX smoke commands run with temporary `HOME`, `XDG_CONFIG_HOME`, and `XDG_CACHE_HOME` values so `scan` and `ghosts` exercise the real binary without traversing the user'"'s full machine.

## Verification Evidence

Commands run from "'`/Users/thekryptodragon/Development/sirsi-pantheon`:

```text
go test ./internal/osiris/
PASS: ok github.com/SirsiMaster/sirsi-pantheon/internal/osiris

